    <note>Wang(2) Jue [1796] Anshi's [1762] great grandson. Dismissed in 1157 because of his association with Qin(1) Gui's [8008] coalition. He established his family (qijia) branch of the lineage in 1132 when he was appointed Yanguan xiancheng, after having been appointed to the title Chengshi lang on the basis of the yin (en) granted when his great grandfather was posthumously awarded the title of Shuwang. Chao Gongsu, WJ, 54.1a-5a; XNYL, 60.7b, 164.11a, 178.8a-8b, 185.22a, 193.21b, 198.10a; Liangchao beiyao, 1.28b; SHY:ZG, 70.52b, 71.1a. CBD, 1, 140.</note>
